# WHAT IS PANDAS 
# NumPy = grid of numbers, no column names 
# Pandas = grid of data with column names,
#  mixed types, and powerful tools 
#
# Think of it like this :
# NumPy array:    Pandas DataFrame:
# [32, 45, 67]    CPU   RAM Disk
# [89, 91, 78]     32   45    67
# [65, 54, 43]     89   91    78
#                  65 54v43
#
#the column names make all the difference
# when working with real data 
